The paper deals with discovering functional dependencies in a database, which is a core topic in database systems (cs.DB). The approach taken is information-theoretic, which suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses measuring the strength of dependencies, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The discovery of dependencies is done through an algorithm, which falls under the category of data mining (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions the use of an optimistic estimator, which is a technique commonly used in reinforcement learning and optimization, both of which fall under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
